{
  "stem": "14900.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I guess we were in a holding pen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Again, about four PM-- this was about 4:30 AM when the coffee would come, maybe four.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Then we would go out, stand at attention, be counted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "In between, they would do lineups and segregation, perpetually selecting people for gas chambers, every single day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We'd have to stand naked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was cold by then, raining, mud, barefoot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Around four in the afternoon they'd bring in another garbage can full of what was called soup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This time gray, lukewarm water with a few pieces, little, maybe one inch cube chunk of potato, rotten piece of cabbage, rotten piece of parsnip or kohlrabi.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "That was it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "That was our daily rations.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I got dysentery.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My mother wasn't doing well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "She'd had a heart condition.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But we were still together and still alive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then one day we went through another line up segregation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I was spattered with mud all the way up the back of my legs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They took one look at me-- I didn't think my mother would make it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "She was weak.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So this time we reversed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Mother stood in front of me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It seems that it was always possible to follow a person to what we guessed was the extermination side.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But you could never come from that side to the still alive side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I was positive that if one of us was chosen for the gas chamber, it would be my mother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "So she went first so I could go after her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I didn't want to live without her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "She passed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "However, it turned out I wasn't going to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We were marched to another lager, lager C.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "It was an all Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
